Key Match Events: Giannis Antetokounmpo had 25 points, 16 rebounds and 8 assists in the team's 121-105 win.
AJ Green had 8 points in the second quarter, while Lillard finally got on the scoreboard.
Pre-Game Insights: San Antonio opened the day by being linked to Jimmy Butler of the Miami Heat, which may or may not affect some of their players.
Khris Middleton will no longer start for the Milwaukee Bucks and officially come off the bench moving forward.
Post-Match Reflections: The Bucks didn't let up in the second half, continuing to dominate the San Antonio Spurs.
The Spurs have now lost three in a row heading into a back-to-back matchup against the LA Lakers at Crypto.com from Jan. 13 to 15.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The Bucks did a fantastic job at denying Victor Wembanyama the ball, with just 10 shots in total.
Others: Victor Wembanyama was limited to just 10 points, 10 rebounds and 3 blocks.
Keldon Johnson had a team-high 24 points off the bench for the Spurs.
